---
title: Sizing
---

p.-text Use responsive sizing utility classes to quickly apply widths and heights on elements.

h3 Notation
p.-text
  | Sizing utility classes can be defined using the format <code>-w-{breakpoint}--{value}</code> for widths and
  | <code>-h-{breakpoint}--{value}</code> for heights.
  | Breakpoints supported are <code>sm</code>, <code>md</code>, <code>lg</code>, and <code>xl</code>.

h3 Width
h4 Target all breakpoints
p.-text Sizing utility classes with no breakpoint defined apply to all screen sizes.
section.a-table.-bordered.-mt3.-mb3
  div
    table.-text(cellpadding='0', cellspacing='0')
      thead
        tr
          th
            div Sizing Class
          th
            div Value
      tbody
        each type in ['auto', '25', '50', '75', '100']
          tr
            td(width='40%')
              code= '-w--' + type
            td
              if (type == 'auto')
                code= 'width: ' + type + ';'
              else
                code= 'width: ' + type + '%;'

h4 Target specific breakpoints
p.-text To target a specific breakpoint, add the breakpoint abbreviation to the class.
section.a-table.-bordered.-mt3.-mb3
  div
    table(cellpadding='0', cellspacing='0')
      thead
        tr
          th
            div Sizing Class
          th
            div Value
      tbody
        each type in ['sm', 'md', 'lg', 'xl']
          each size in ['auto', '25', '50', '75', '100']
            tr
              td.-text(width='40%')
                code= '-w-' + type + '--' + size
              td.-text Visible only from <code>#{type}</code>

h3 Examples
.example.-mb3
  .-p3
    .-text.-b1.-p3.-m1.-w--auto(style="background:#E4F2CE;border-color:#C6DBA7;") -w--auto
    .-text.-b1.-p3.-m1.-w--25(style="background:#E4F2CE;border-color:#C6DBA7;") -w--25
    .-text.-b1.-p3.-m1.-w--50(style="background:#E4F2CE;border-color:#C6DBA7;") -w--50
    .-text.-b1.-p3.-m1.-w-md--75(style="background:#E4F2CE;border-color:#C6DBA7;") -w-md--75
    .-text.-b1.-p3.-m1.-w-xl--50(style="background:#E4F2CE;border-color:#C6DBA7;") -w-xl--50
  :code(lang="html")
    <!-- width auto on all breakpoints -->
    <div class="-w--auto"></div>
    <!-- width 25% on all breakpoints -->
    <div class="-w--25"></div>
    <!-- width 50% on all breakpoints -->
    <div class="-w--50"></div>
    <!-- width 75% from md -->
    <div class="-w-md--75"></div>
    <!-- width 50% from xl -->
    <div class="-w-xl--50"></div>

